CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 4, 1960, pg. 20 reads: "Outstanding Brothers - "The Sheffield boys." sons of the Rev. Eugene and Bessie Sheffield of New Brighton, are outstanding in Beaver County...Calvin L. (left photo) recently received an academic-athletic scholarship to study dentistry at the University of Pittsburgh for his scholastic and athletic ability. He is shown with several of the many trophies which he won on the hard court.  Arthur Lee (Archie), shown in center, also was an outstanding  basketball player and is headed for a civil engineering course at Geneva College...-Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Calvin L. or Arthur Lee "Archie" Sheffield holding trophy, standing in interior with knotty pine paneling, bookcase with books and basketball trophies
